Petrobras to Raise Pre-Salt Investments by 63%, Estado Says

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-04-30T13:46:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/petrobras-to-raise-pre-salt-investments-by-63-estado-says.html
Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  will boost
planned investments in pre-salt oil reserves in Brazil’s Santos
basin by 63 percent, Estado de Sao Paulo newspaper  reported ,
citing Chief Financial Officer Almir Barbassa.  Of the $73 billion of planned investments in the Santos
basin, $54 billion will come from Petrobras and the balance from
its partners, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said.  The decision was taken by the company’s board yesterday,
the newspaper said. Petrobras will announce its new five-year
investment plan by the end of May, according to Estado.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 